<font color="#FF0000">RESPONSE TO ART</font><br>
<tt>Mon Oct  6 21:25:24 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Art,<br><br>
You were just up the road from me about one hour. My wife was a contestant for &quot;Fairest Of the Fair&quot; at the Appy Fair about 20 years ago - she's quite a bit younger than me. She played there this year with the bluegrtass band she is in.<br><br>
In order to stay on the subject of Vietnam, I have often credited my moving to the country many years ago to my ability to cope. Life has always been an adventure for me.<br><br>
I bought a little homestead in the hills and learned how to put my energy into surviving. Winters can be tough here, but some of my most cherished memories have been when I was snowbound with my family.<br><br>
People take care of each other here, just like we did in Vietnam.
<p><code>-- wingman@greene..xtn.net  (Tom Dier) </code><p>


